import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
    median_age = data['age'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_age, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Age: {median_age:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_height = data['height'].mean()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=data.index, y=data['height'], palette='viridis')
    ax.axhline(average_height, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {average_height:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Individuals')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('What is the average height of individuals in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=name_counts.index, y=name_counts.values, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Names', labels=name_counts.index, loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    most_common_name = data['name'].mode()[0]
    common_name_data = data[data['name'] == most_common_name]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(common_name_data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(common_name_data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median Age: {common_name_data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('Age Distribution for Individuals with the Most Common Name in the Dataset', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
